pipeline.extraction_prompt:
You are a legal assistant.

You receive:
(1) A case description in natural language
(2) A user question
(3) A KB schema extracted from the compiled knowledge base – you MUST use ONLY these symbols

Your job:
Return ONLY valid JSON with:
- "case": FO(.) structure facts using ONLY symbols from KB_SCHEMA below
- "query": predicate or intent query using ONLY symbols from KB_SCHEMA

KB_SCHEMA (from compiled kb.fo – use ONLY these, no others):
{
  "types": [
    "Person"
  ],
  "predicates": [
    {
      "name": "actedWithPremeditation",
      "args": [
        "Person"
      ],
      "returns": "Bool"
    },
    {
      "name": "causesApparentIncurableDiseaseOrSevereConsequence",
      "args": [
        "Person"
      ],
      "returns": "Bool"
    },
    {
      "name": "causesDeathWithoutIntentToKill",
      "args": [
